d 'KYPSHIFT': module to test shifts between I(1) and I(0) regimes at unknown dates (Kejriwal-Yu-Perron 2020) 
d
d   kypshift implements the wild bootstrap tests of Kejriwal, Yu,
d and Perron (2020, Journal of Time Series Analysis) for multiple
d shifts between I(1) and I(0) regimes, with the number of breaks
d and the break dates unknown, and with tests that remain valid
d under heteroskedasticity. The number and dates of the breaks are
d estimated by the sequential procedure of the paper, and the
d diagnostics of its Tables I and II are reproduced. The
d directional statistics of Kejriwal, Perron, and Zhou (2013,
d Econometric Theory), which identify whether the series starts in
d an I(1) or an I(0) regime, are also reported; the asympcv option
d adds their asymptotic critical values, the Bai-Perron critical
d values, and the hybrid decision of that paper. 
d
d KW: unit root tests
d KW: stationarity
d KW: break points
d
d Requires: Stata version 16
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260718
d
d Author: Ozan Eruygur,  Ankara Haci Bayram Veli University
d Support: email eruygur@@gmail.com
d
f kypshift.ado
